Package <Unnamed>

Class Summary
Actor An actor is any object that has a degree of autonomy or intelligent input (Human / AIManager) dictating the object's behavior ingame Subclass of GameObject
AIManager Strategy management behind the AI (Ghost objects)
AStarHeuristic A heuristic that uses the tile that is closest to the target as the next best tile.
EditorFrame This code was edited or generated using CloudGarden's Jigloo SWT/Swing GUI Builder, which is free for non-commercial use.
EditorMarker The EditorMarker is used by the StateEditor for navigation and selecting tiles on the map EditorMarker is NOT tracked inside the Map EditorMarker is a subclass of GameObject
Game The Game Supervisor.
GameObject A game object is anything on the pacman grid (wall, cherry, ghost, player).
Ghost The Ghost class is the primary enemy in Pacman.
Item Item objects are GameObject's that can be manipulated by the Player on the map (teleports, dots, powerups, fruit) Item is a subclass of GameObject
JPacmanGame The entry point of the program
Map Map class keeps track objects on the playing grid, helper methods to make movement decisions, and export/import methods for the editor
Path A path determined by some path finding algorithm.
PathFinder A path finder implementation that uses the AStar heuristic based algorithm to determine a path.
Player Player (pacman) is the object controlled by the human playing the game Player is a subclass of Actor
State A State is a mode of the program where input and functionality are radically different from others portions of the program.
StateEditor The StateEditor is a mode of the program that allows the user to create and modify map files that can be played in StateGame.
StateGame StateGame is a mode of the program where the user can play the game of Pacman various maps StateGame is a subclass of State
StateMenu StateMenu is a graphical representation that allows users to switch into other States of the program like the Game and editor
StateScoreboard StateScoreboard is a mode of the program that allows the user to view (and sometimes modify) scores set in StateGame StateScoreboard is a subclass of State
